<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'>When
I checkpoint my openmpi application using ompi_checkpoint, I see that top
command suddenly shows some really huge numbers in &quot;CPU %&quot; field such
as 150% 200% etc. After sometime, these numbers do come back to the normal numbers
under 100%. This happens exactly around the time checkpoint is completed and
when the processes are resuming the execution.</span><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'>Another
behavior I have seen is that one MPI process starts to show different elapsed
time than its peers. Is it because checkpoint happened on behalf of this
process?</span><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'>For
your reference, I am using open mpi 1.3.4 and BLCR 0.8.2 for checkpointing.</span><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'>Thanks<br>
Anand</span><o:p></o:p></p>

